blog.description:
Hi everyone! :) I am a Canadian nerdy teacher😉 welcome to my blog!❤️This is a completely random blog which I started December 19, 2010 & it consists of things that I am obsessed with/find cool at the time. I tend to blog a lot about tv shows or books and things from my childhood (sailor moon❤️❤️) . Other than reading & watching tv I also enjoy anime, video games, musicals, The Body Shop/skin care products, keeping up with a few Youtubers (Safiya Nyguard, The Try Guys and a few others) , i also love disney and baking! A few of my current favourite shows are THIS IS US❤️, Miraculous Ladybug, Riverdale, Game of Thrones, Brooklyn Nine-Nine, The Good Place, Star vs The Forces of Evil, Jane the Virgin, The Unbreakable Kimmy Schmidt, Anne with an E, A Series Of Unfortunate Events, and Stranger Things (among many many other awesome shows, I'm a bit of a tv addict lol). A few recent video games I played and liked are all free mobile games: Stranger Things The Game, 7 years from now, and now currently playing independent game called Doom&Destiny (original version, i like the old school graphics of older version of this game) I've also been kinda playing that Choices phone game (the story called Open Heart specifically). I love movies from Ghibli to Disney to star wars to superhero to rom coms, most recent movies that I've seen are Spiderman into the Spider-Verse, Ralph Breaks the internet and The Blind Side.❤️❤️

summary: Idk why everyone seems to think Bran can see the future? Like he gets glimpses through green dreams but those are largely...
body:
Idk why everyone seems to think Bran can see the future? Like he gets glimpses through green dreams but those are largely metaphorical (I.e “the sea coming to Winterfell” = the Greyjoys sacking it) and at best tiny flashes and glimpses (I.e seeing a shadow of a dragon flying over KL and seeing the sept exploding). Other than that he can’t see any concrete future in the same way he can view past events because the future hasn’t happened yet.

I also think once you understand that, it definitely humanizes him a lot because you realize that he really doesn’t know if they will win or not and he is just as scared and unsure as everyone else. So him saying “how do you know there’s an after” wasn’t him implying Jaime’s or his own deaths he just truly doesn’t know if they will win.
